						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarāja III. Year 26: Śaka 1163 = A.D. 1241.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of gold for maintaining one perpetual lamp in the temple of Mayindīśvaram Uḍaiyār, by a <hi rend="italic">vāṇiyaṉ</hi>, Arumbākkiḻān Nāyan for the welfare of his son Cāmāḻvān Pammāḻvāṉ. The money seems to have been invested in buying a piece of land.</p>						

